/**
 * mono_reverse: canonical note on the `rev_<Type>` helper pattern.
 *
 * This module intentionally defines no functions. It exists as a single place
 * for the note below, so greps for the shared convention land here instead of
 * in eight per-file copies.
 *
 * Owns:
 * - The rationale note below.
 *
 * Does not own:
 * - The type-specific reverse helpers themselves (`rev_i64s`,
 *   `rev_hir_expr`, `rev_mir_param`, `rev_lir_atom`, `reverse_tokens`, etc.).
 *   Those stay local to each module because they reference IR types that must
 *   not leak into a shared module — consolidating them would create a central
 *   god-module importing from every IR/frontend/backend file.
 *
 * Monomorphic reverse helpers, status: the per-file `rev_<Type>` helpers exist
 * as historical workarounds for a self-hosted-codegen issue with generic
 * `std:list.reverse` ("type mismatch: expected i64 but nothing on stack" when
 * running the emitted binary). That issue no longer reproduces: a generic
 * `list.reverse` over string, i64, and user-defined variant lists now builds
 * and runs correctly under the self-hosted compiler. The shared `[string]`
 * reverser (formerly the standalone listrev helper) has been migrated to
 * `list.reverse` accordingly. The remaining per-file `rev_<Type>` helpers can
 * now be migrated to `list.reverse` family-wide as a separate cleanup; until
 * then they remain a behavior-preserving local convention.
 */
